,"lifeSummary":"當Isabella de St. Pierre於大約1343年出生在英國爾時，她的父親Urian de Sancto Pierre15歲，母親Agnes de Braose18歲。她於1380年與Walter Cokesey結婚。他們至少是1個兒子和1個女兒的父母。她去世於大約1405年享年64歲。"},"zh-hans":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"大约1343年–大约1405年","1343–1405":"1343年–1405年","1360–Male":"1360年–殁","1343–1404":"1343年–1404年","1358–Female":"1358年–殁","1385–1407":"1385年–1407年","1329–1376":"1329年–1376年","1327–Female":"1327年–殁","1385":"1385年","1382":"1382年","1360":"1360年","1380":"1380年","Abt 1405":"大约1405年","1404":"1404年","1327":"1327年","1358":"1358年","1376":"1376年","1343":"1343年","about 1343":"大约1343年","1407":"1407年","1329":"1329年","about 1340":"大约1340年","1405":"1405年","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"英国英格兰武斯特斯爾吉德米斯特","Cheshire, England":"英国爾","lifeSummary":"当Isabella de St. Pierre于大约1343年出生在英国爾时，她的父亲Urian de Sancto Pierre15岁，母亲Agnes de Braose18岁。她于1380年与Walter Cokesey结婚。他们至少是1个儿子和1个女儿的父母。她去世于大约1405年享年64岁。"},"hr":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"oko 1343.–oko 1405.","1343–1405":"1343–1405","1360–Male":"1360–preminuo","1343–1404":"1343–1404.","1358–Female":"1358.–preminula","1385–1407":"1385.–1407","1329–1376":"1329–1376.","1327–Female":"1327–preminula","1385":"1385.","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380.","Abt 1405":"oko 1405.","1404":"1404.","1327":"1327","1358":"1358.","1376":"1376.","1343":"1343","about 1343":"oko 1343.","1407":"1407","1329":"1329","about 1340":"oko 1340.","1405":"1405","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, Engleska, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"cs":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"okolo 1343–okolo 1405","1343–1405":"1343–1405","1360–Male":"1360–Zesnulý","1343–1404":"1343–1404","1358–Female":"1358–Zesnulá","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1329–1376":"1329–1376","1327–Female":"1327–Zesnulá","1385":"1385","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1405":"okolo 1405","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","about 1343":"okolo 1343","1407":"1407","1329":"1329","about 1340":"okolo 1340","1405":"1405","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, Anglie, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Anglie"},"da":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"omkring 1343–omkring 1405","1343–1405":"1343–1405","1360–Male":"1360–Afdød","1343–1404":"1343–1404","1358–Female":"1358–Afdød","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1329–1376":"1329–1376","1327–Female":"1327–Afdød","1385":"1385","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1405":"omkring 1405","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","about 1343":"omkring 1343","1407":"1407","1329":"1329","about 1340":"omkring 1340","1405":"1405","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"nl":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"circa 1343–circa 1405","1343–1405":"1343–1405","1360–Male":"1360–Overleden","1343–1404":"1343–1404","1358–Female":"1358–Overleden","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1329–1376":"1329–1376","1327–Female":"1327–Overleden","1385":"1385","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1405":"circa 1405","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","about 1343":"circa 1343","1407":"1407","1329":"1329","about 1340":"circa 1340","1405":"1405","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England"},"en":{"about 1343–Abt 1405":"about 1343–about 1405","1343–1405":"1343–1405","1360–Male":"1360–Deceased","1343–1404":"1343–1404","1358–Female":"1358–Deceased","1385–1407":"1385–1407","1329–1376":"1329–1376","1327–Female":"1327–Deceased","1385":"1385","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","1380":"1380","Abt 1405":"about 1405","1404":"1404","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1376":"1376","1343":"1343","about 1343":"about 1343","1407":"1407","1329":"1329","about 1340":"about 1340","1405":"1405","Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England":"Kidderminster, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"St.","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Southern French: variant of   St  .   Romain  ."],"variants":[{"name":"St","meanings":["Southern French: variant of   St  .   Romain  ."]},{"name":"Romain","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French/Haitian Alain, Altagrace, Aurore, Camille, Dominique, Edele, Georges, Henri, Jacques, Jean-Marie, Jean-Michel, Jeanmarie.","French, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and English: variant of   Roman  ."]}]},{"name":"Pierre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Jacques, Antoine, Yves, Michel, Jean Claude, Mireille, Jean Robert, Francois, Monique, Raoul, Serge.","French, Walloon, West Indian (mainly Haiti), and Mauritian:","from the personal name <i>Pierre</i>, French form of   Peter   (see also below). This is one of the most frequent surnames in Haiti (along with   Jean   and   Joseph  ) and in Saint Martin. It is also established elsewhere in the West Indies (e.g. in Trinidad and Tobago, Saint Lucia, Grenada, and Bahamas)."],"variants":[{"name":"Perrault","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Gisele, Jacques, Marcel, Roch, Alphonse, Andre, Donat, Emile, Francoise, Gaston, Ghislaine.","French: from a pet form of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Paro  ,   Parro  ,   Parrow  ,   Pearo  ,   Perault  ,   Pero  ,   Perreault  ,   Perro  ,   Perrot  , and   Perrow  .","History: Jacques Perrault/Perrot <i>dit</i> Villedaigre from Mons in Charente-Maritime, France, married Michelle Le Flot in Quebec City, QC, in 1654. Nicolas Perrault/Perrot from Darcey in Côte-d’Or married Madeleine Raclos in QC in 1671. Pierre Perrault from France married Geneviève Duclos in QC <i>c.</i> 1686. François Perrault from Cosne-Cours-sur-Loire in Nièvre married Jeanne-Suzanne Pagé in Quebec City, QC, in 1715. — In North America, this surname was originally (also) a secondary surname or <i>dit</i> (‘also called’) name, borne by Louis Leparon <i>dit</i> Perrault (a son of Pierre Leparon from Derval in Loire-Atlantique, France), who married Marie-Josèphe Normandeau in Quebec City, QC, in 1751. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (along with its altered forms <i>Perrow</i> and <i>Pero</i>) and also in the similar registers of the Huguenot Society of America and of the Huguenot Society of the Founders of Manakin in the Colony of Virginia. The Huguenot ancestor was Charles Perrault from Bordeaux in France, one of the settlers of Manakin, VA, in the early 1700s. However, his descendants bear only altered forms of the surname, such as <i>Perrow</i> and <i>Perow</i>."]},{"name":"Perot","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Alphonse, Antoine, Philippe, Remy.","French (<b>Pérot</b>): from a pet form of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perrow  .","Altered form of French   Perret  , a cognate of 1 above."]},{"name":"Lapierre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Armand, Andre, Lucien, Normand, Adrien, Alcide, Aristide, Arnaud, Julien, Pierre, Aime.","French, Walloon, and Flemish:","topographic name, with fused French feminine definite article <i>la</i>, for someone who lived on a patch of stony soil or by a large outcrop of rock, from Old French <i>pierre</i> ‘stone, rock’ (compare   Pierre   2); or a habitational name from any of various places called Lapierre or La Pierre in France and Belgium (Wallonia), with the same meaning."]},{"name":"Paret","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Philippe, Pierre.  Spanish Joaquin, Alberto, Caridad, Eduardo, Eugenio, Lourdes, Patricio, Wilfredo.","French: habitational name from (Le) Paret, the name of several places in various parts of France, ultimately derived from Latin <i>paries</i>, genitive <i>parietis</i> ‘wall’ (compare 3 below).","French: from a pet form of the personal name   Pierre  ."]},{"name":"Peregoy","meanings":["Americanized form of French <b>Périgord</b>: habitational name from Périgord, the name of a former province in France, of Gaulish origin.","Alternatively, an Americanized form of northwestern French <b>Périgois</b>, which may possibly be a cognate of 1 above, or, more likely, a regional derivative of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Pedigo  ,   Perigo  ,   Perrigo  , and   Pherigo  .","History: The progenitor of the Peregoys was Joseph Peregoy, a Frenchman who came to Baltimore County, MD, in 1685. In North America his surname was first recorded as <i>Peregois</i> and later spelled in many other ways, including <i>Perigo</i>, <i>Perigoe</i>, and <i>Perrigo</i>. The majority of his descendants (through his son Henry) bear the surname   Pedigo  ."]},{"name":"Pearre","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre.","Possibly also an altered form of French   Pierre  .","Altered form of English   Perry  ."]},{"name":"Peron","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Cecile, Fernand, Herve, Michel, Philippe, Virginie.","French (<b>Péron</b>): from a pet form of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  . Compare   Perron   1 and 2.","Breton (<b>Péron</b>, rarely <b>Le Péron</b>): variant of <b>Pédron</b> (see   Pedron  )."]},{"name":"Peter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Hans, Kurt, Otto, Ernst, Fritz, Heinz, Helmut, Horst, Kaspar, Klaus, Siegfried, Wolfgang.","English, Scottish, German, Dutch, French (Alsace and Lorraine), Czech (Moravian), Slovak, Croatian, and Slovenian; Hungarian (<b>Péter</b>): from the personal name <i>Peter</i> (Greek <i>Petros</i>, from <i>petra</i> ‘rock’). The personal name was popular throughout Christian Europe in the Middle Ages, having been bestowed by Christ as a byname on the apostle Simon bar Jonah, the brother of Andrew. The name was chosen by Christ for its symbolic significance (John 1:42, Matt. 16:18); Saint Peter is regarded as the founding head of the Christian Church in view of Christ's saying, ‘Thou art Peter and upon this rock I will build my Church’. In Christian Germany in the early Middle Ages this was the most frequent personal name of non-ancient Germanic origin until the 14th century. In North America, this surname has also absorbed cognates from other languages, for example Czech   Petr  , Polish <b>Piotr</b> and <b>Pietr</b>, Albanian <b>Pjetri</b> (from the personal name <i>Pjetër</i>, definite form <i>Pjetri</i>), and also their derivatives (see examples at   Peterson  ). It has also been adopted as a surname by Ashkenazic Jews."]},{"name":"Perret","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Pierre, Emile, Jacques, Michel, Andree, Dominique, Etienne, Fernand, Henri, Solange.","French: from a pet form of the Old French personal name <i>Perre</i>, a variant of   Pierre  , French form of   Peter  .","English (Somerset, Gloucestershire and Wiltshire): variant of   Parrott  ."]},{"name":"Patriquin","meanings":["Altered form of French <b>Petrequin</b>: from a pet form of <i>Petre</i>, a regional variant of the personal name   Pierre   ‘Peter’."]}]},{"name":"Isabella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."],"variants":[{"name":"Isobella","meanings":["form of   Isabel  , which has been popular in England since the 18th century and has recently become the preferred form of the name."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks